parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt retraction system can cause the seat belt to remain stuck or not retract properly, which can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract back when the door is closed
the seat belt leaves the consumer belted in unless the door is slightly open
the seat belt does not lock upon applying the brakes
the plastic housing on the female side of the buckle comes off
the seat belt buckle disintegrates
the seat belt locks up before the passengers can even get them on
the automatic seat belt won't go across unless the consumer pulls the shoulder belt part over them
the shoulder belt won't work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, which can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle disintegrates
the male buckle won't go into the female portion
the buckle is inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt can cause the seat belt to become stuck or not work properly, which can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The motorized seat belt quits moving along the channel in the door track
the motorized seat belt failed prior to recall
the motorized seat belt caught fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Leaks and Fuel Odor Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks and strong fuel odors can increase the risk of fire, explosion, and accidents, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from underneath the vehicle
fuel leaks when driving up or down hills
strong fuel odor present at all times
smell of raw gas when the gas tank is more than half full
fuel tank leaks at the tank neck and tank meet
fuel tank leaks where the filler vent pipe enters the gas tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, resulting in loss of control, stalling, and potential accidents. Additionally, electrical system failures can lead to engine compartment fires, which can result in vehicle damage or total loss.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
failure of electrical accessories such as fan/heater and air conditioning
vehicle stalling without warning
inability to move the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Ignition failure
cold starter switch failure
difficulty starting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can result in vehicle damage or total loss, and potentially cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke or flames coming from the engine compartment
often near the windshield or on the left side of the vehicle.
